text: My cousin who is visiting from Thailand wanted to go see this movie, "Spy" with Melissa McCarthy. I've seen the majority of films with Melissa McCarthy. My Mom, sister, cousin, and I went out to see this film earlier today. This "Spy" film is one of the BEST comedies I've seen in a long time. I haven't laughed so much in a long time. My sister, cousin, Mom, & I were laughing and smiling through many parts of this movie. When this movie is released on DVD, I'm going to go buy it. I think I'm going to buy some DVDs of movies that Melissa McCarthy has acted in. I've seen the majority of Melissa McCarthy's work. She is SO talented and funny. I love that she is such a hardworking and memorable Midwestern gal! She was good in "Tammy", "Bridesmaids", "Identity Thief", and that tv series, "Mike & Molly". I haven't seen "The Heat" yet with Sandra Bullock.  This movie is SO GOOD that I bet there will be a "Spy 2" movie in the future! This movies is very entertaining. And I just laughed so much. It made me smile to hear so many people laughing in the audience, too. This was the kind of movie I needed to see after having such a rough year. If you want to see a movie that makes you forget about your real world problems and makes you laugh, smile, and feel good, go watch this "Spy" movie. It's great! Also, it's nice to see Rose Byrne and Melissa McCarthy have a reunion in this movie, since they were both in "Bridesmaids" together. Jason Statham should do more comedic roles, too. 50 Cent is in this movie, too! Melissa McCarthy's real life husband makes a cameo appearance in this movie. I'm so glad that I got to see this movie with my cousin, sister, and Mom! :-)

text: Spy was definitely the most positive surprise I've ever encountered when it comes to movies. Despite Melissa McCarthy's skills as an actress, the subject and trailers gave a picture about another cheap, Adam Sandler-styled cheap goofball comedy with lousy humor meant to speak for the lowest common denominator. So I went to see it as another "brains on a hanger"-experience. But what I encountered: quite intelligent action comedy with some nice satire for spy film cliches, sane amount of feminist message, entertaining action scenes, and most important; extremely clever sitcom and great humor in different kind of forms. Characters are also hilariously sharpened, and both casting and acting performances are such admirable work. Academic level has traditionally overlooked the whole genre of comedy, so I'm not really expecting Spy to achieve any Oscar-nominations. But I still appreciate this well made and funny movie.
